TO THE TROLLS: 
I don't usually feed the trolls but there's people out there that have zero idea how this press event worked, so I thought I'd share.
This is the only riding shot I have of me from the S1000RR event. Its not some great knee dragging, lightening fast photo coz NO TIME! 
I got to the track on the day of the event with 2 fifteen minute riding slots scheduled for me. Unfortunately there were crashes and so the only display bike that was given to a group of about 65 journos + buyers was also taken away to ride on the track. We were now left with 6 bikes between us all to film statics and get to ride the bike on the track for the first time. The journos of course had to be given a lot more time.

Now, it unfortunately happened to also be my first time at BIC on a bike and its not a short track that my "superbrain" could grasp it in a lap. After I started to figure the bike out a little, my time was up and I didn't get to film any riding or cornering footage with my crew.  It was hella disappointing for me more than any of you because after my last S1000RR video, I had every hope to get some even better corners on video. 
So before you point fingers at any journo or content creator in the future for lack of a mad video, please know that we're putting in our all to bring that content out for you. I started BikeWithGirl 3yrs ago to share MY experiences of riding different machines and I'll keep trying my hardest  to bring you guys the best Moto content possible. And of course improve my skills along the way, coz like I keep saying, I aint no expert! üôèüèº #PSA

I landed up at the BIC bright and early and after much convincing @vickyjaising handed over the @bmwmotorrad_in S1000RR (standard variant) to me. @okrishabh had to film some tracking shots of me for the YT video so it started off as a slow, painful ride behind an Innova. üò©
After a point I just couldn't take it that my first few laps on the brand new 2020 S1000RR had me experiencing it at a bugging 40kph on one of the fastest race tracks I know. So I just opened gas and flew off the back straight at the BIC. Before I knew it my time was up. But this was the sweaty grin that the new S1000RR left me with...and of course a yelling @okrishabh "Dude where the hell did you go?" üòÇ

üåπ MY LIL STORY üåπ
I bumped into a few friends that I grew up with in Pune a few days ago and everybody was shocked at my career choices "Priyanka how did you outta all us girls, take up things like modelling and motorcycles üòµ? If anything we thought you'd have had kids by nowü§∞üèª. Your parents were the strictest growing up!"
Even though my Mum-dad are on Instagram and will prolly be the first to read this, I am gonna say, yes they were not as chill as most others parents in the society we grew up in. At 15, all I knew was that I will be married at 21 to a boy they choose for me. That was the only goal I knew because its so normal in India.üòûüòû
Everytime in the recent past I have spoken about the hurdles of growing up a girl in a Punjabi household, I've gotten some flak , "You're lying. We've seen your dad on video and he's so cool with letting his daughter do everything she wants to". The truth is, he wasn't always like that üôÇ. Its taken years of standing my ground, being a 100% sure of my decisions and  doing things they didn't approve of at all. But the hurdles, they make it all worthwhile ‚ù§Ô∏è. Because today even after hurting my folks, they've begun to understand that their daughter is not a bad, "loose" girl. She just wants different things for herself. So if you're in a space (boy or girl) where you want a different life for you, be sure to hustle and make it happen. ‚ù§Ô∏è
#Empower #Educate #inspire
.
.
üì∏ @x_vishaldubey

Throwback to the 2014, the day I sold my first bike, The R15 ver.1. This picture was taken by @rishaadmody the day the buyer was coming to finally take the bike. He said "Smile, it's your last pic with her", but instead the tears won't stopüò•. It was an emotional few days because I really didn't want to let her go but I had out of nowhere developed a lower back issue which I battled for over 2 yrs. After multiple tests, the doc figured it was the supersport/committed riding posture on the R15 that was causing it. I tried my all to sit up straight on it and ride, made every adjustment I possibly could from my end but nothing helped and the situation with my back got so bad that I was in agony all the time. üòß

She was the bike that started it all, the bike I fought my family for and lastly the bike that made everyone realize that their lil girl has grown up, knows what she wants and will go for it at any cost! ‚ù§Ô∏è
#LifeLesson
.
.

I'm in a beautiful place today thanks to the motorcycles, cars, travel, my family and YOU GUYS ‚ù§Ô∏è. The success, the joy of achievement is everything. But that doesn't trump all... There is a mountain of stress to think up different content ideas every day and to survive the hate, to live out of a gear bag constantly and of course the anxiety that is the gift of social media!
